    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Film Makers And the Abuser</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>David Van Taylor letter on Ted Conover's Mar 30 article on making of documentary film It Ain't Love, on teenage domestic violence; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I would (I hope) never resort to violence against a lover. Nevertheless, reading Brian's description of how he came to batter Irene, and his observations about why such things happen, I found him to be a self-aware young man struggling with the difficult issues life presents us all. His open soul-searching, encouraged by the film makers, made him more sympathetic, not less so.</p>
        <p>David Van Taylor  New York</p>
      </block>
